  "text": "In Figure 15 , different numbers of UEs are considered to evaluate energy efficiency performance. For all the densities, the least efficiency is achieved with no PC. In the most dense scenario, the best efficiency can be observed under the second configuration, min / min [see [CITATION_1] ]. As it is expected with the reduction of densities, energy efficiency is increased. However, after a certain average energy efficiency level, no significant improvements could be observed. ",
